{"word":"γέλοιος","slug":"γέλοιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γέλοιος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γελάω'><el>γελάω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>causing laughter, laughable</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>γελοῖα</el> <i>jests</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of persons, <i>causing laughter, ridiculous</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}